<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1530 GMT, August 12 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN -- The fugitive German owner of a Miami beach houseboat
used by the suspected murderer of fashion guru Gianni Versace has
been arrested in Germany on charges of fraud and tax evasion.
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Indonesia today began the construction of the
world's tallest tower -- the Jakarta Tower here with a ceremony
officiated at by Minister/State Secretary Moerdiono.
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Estonia warned the Russian town of Ivangorod on
Monday that it would cut the town's water supply if it did not
settle a debt to the Estonian suppliers.
</P>
<P>
DHAKA -- Leader of the opposition Bangladesh Nationalist party
(BNP) Khaleda Zia today accused the government of selling out the
country's sovereignty to its neighboring India.
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Some 2,000 Palestinians marched in the West Bank
city of Nablus today to protest against Israeli punitive measures
against the Palestinians taken after the suicide bombing attacks
in Jerusalem on July 30.
</P>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- European Humanitarian Commissioner Emma Bonino
today described the correct and full implementation of the
oil-for-food program as being in the interests of the Iraqi people.
</P>
<P>
KATHMANDU -- Ram Chandra Poudyal is to resign as speaker of the
Lower House of Nepal, sources close to Poudyal said today.
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- About 65 people were feared drowned in floods in
Shimla and Kinnaur districts of Himachal Pradesh of northwestern
India on Monday, local press reports said today.
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- Indian Prime Minister Inder Kumar Gujral said he
was confident the talks between India and Pakistan would succeed
and that the two neighboring countries would find a way out on the
disputed Kashmir issue, local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG -- South Africa's ruling African National Congress
(ANC) is planning to push for the total removal of white dominance
in all spheres of power, including the economy, civil service,
security forces and media control. 
</P>
</TEXT>
