<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mullin Joins Pacers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The Indiana Pacers with a new
coach Larry Bird, broght Chris Mullin, five time NBA All-Star
forward, onto the club.
</P>
<P>
The Pacers obtained 1992 Olympic "Dream Team" mate Mullin from
the Golden State Tuesday in exchange for center Erick Dampier and
forward Duane Ferrell.
</P>
<P>
Mullin, 34, had played his entire 12-year NBA career with the
Warriors but was the subject of numerous trade rumors over the
past several years. He is in the final season of a nine-year
contract with a rebuilding club.
</P>
<P>
After missing an average of 35 games per season over a
four-year span, Mullin played 79 games last year and averaged 14.5
points and 4.1 assists. He averaged more than 25 points a game
from the 1988-89 to 1992-93 seasons.
</P>
<P>
The deal gives Indiana the league's most potent outside
shooting combination with Mullin, 1996 Olympic "Dream Team III"
guard Reggie Miller and rookie Austin Croshere.  
</P>
</TEXT>
