<HEADLINE> Malawi President Visits Swaziland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Malawi President Bakili
Muluzi started a three-day state visit to Swaziland today at the
invitation of King Mswati III, reported the South African Press
Association today.
</P>
<P>
Muluzi, accompanied by a team of 37 government officials, was
greeted by the King, Prime Minister Sibusisoi Dlamini and other
government ministers at Matsapa Airport on his arrival.
</P>
<P>
At the welcoming ceremony at the airport, Dlamini said the
challenges facing the two countries were similar.
</P>
<P>
It was important for Swaziland and Malawi to strengthen
bilateral relations, he noted, because the two countries were
both land-locked.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Swaziland, the president, who had earlier
had a private meeting with King Mswati, was also expected to hold
discussions on the long-term development strategies of the two
countries. 
</P>
