still stay in a military base in Elbasan, 35 kilometers southeast
of Tirana.
</P>
<P>
In April, a total of more than 700 Greek troops arrived in
Albania as part of the multinational force to protect the speedy
distribution of humanitarian aid and the June 29 general elections
in the neighboring country.
</P>
<P>
The largest part of the Greek troops returned home at the
beginning of this month. 
