This was disclosed by Tanzanian Defense and National Service
Minister Edgar Maokola Majogo at the current session of the
National Assembly in Dodoma today.
</P>
<P>
The refugees, including some soldiers, fled their country
during civil strifes, said Majogo, adding that the situation is
calming down in that central African country with Laurent
kabila's administration.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that during the year 1997/98, the situation
in Tanzania was calm and border areas were peaceful with
exception to those bordering Burundi and the Republic of Congo.
</P>
<P>
Areas bordering Tanzania and the democratic Congo were tense
due to a big number of Congolese refugees who were fleeing their
country into Tanzania because of civil strifes there, he said.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania is working closely with defense mechanism in the
African region, particularly the Southern African Development
Community (SADC) and the East African Community (EAC), to ensure
peace prevailed and in combating different crimes, according to
Majogo. 
