<HEADLINE> Russian Defense Ministry on Air Force Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 12 (Xinhua) -- As a result of integration of
the Russian Air Force with air defense troops will reduce the
number of general-held posts from 330 to 130, the Itar-Tass news
agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
According to a Defense Ministry spokesman, the integration is
to give rise to single type of troops, the Russian Air Force.
</P>
<P>
He said the military reform, which is to re-make the army of
1,700,000 into a compact 1,200,000, will reduce the present Air
Force personnel 3.18 times, including a 2.9 time decrease in the
number of flyers and a 4.64 time decrease in the sergeant and
private personnel.
</P>
<P>
The ministry press service said that the Air Force personnel
has dwindled from 500,000 in 1991 to the present 170,000 and the
aircraft fleet from 11,000 to 5,000. The number of
aircraft-repairing factories has decreased from 57 to 23.
</P>
<P>
Most of the lay-offs involved managerial personnel and
duplicate services, while combat units remained intact, the press
service said.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Air Force is currently made of 21 air divisions and
over 100 regiments.
</P>
<P>
The military reform of the Air force will put the combat
airpower under operational command of military district
commanders, and the long-haul and transport airpower is to remain
under the Air Force commander.
</P>
<P>
According to the press service, the planned integration of
airpowers and air defense troops into the single Air Force would
facilitate the adoption of computer control of airfield and
logistic services, applications of sophisticated space mission
systems and implementation of a program of rearmament with new
hardware and air-to-ground and air-to-air weapons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970813.0030 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-13 </DATE_TIME>
