<HEADLINE> Liberian Refugees in Guinea Eager to Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Liberian refugees in neighboring
Guinea are eager to go home as Guinea is moving to re-establish
its official relations with Liberia.
</P>
<P>
A Nigeria Television Authority report tonight said although
the refugees, estimated at 400,000, did not participated in
Liberia's elections in July, they said they were satisfied with
the outcome.
</P>
<P>
