<HEADLINE> U.S. Computer Retailer Reports Record Earnings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 13 (Xinhua) -- CompUSA Inc., America's Largest
Computer retailer, today announced record earnings for both the
fourth quarter and the fiscal year ended June 28, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The company said that its net sales for the quarter ended June
28, increased 23 percent to 1.15 billion U.S. dollars over the
same quarter in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Its net income jumped 94 percent for the fourth quarter of
fiscal 1997 to a record 22.9 million U.S. dollars, compared with
the net income of 11.8 million dollars, for the fourth quarter of
fiscal 1996.
</P>
<P>
Net sales for the fiscal year ended June 28, 1997 increased 22
percent to 4.61 billion U.S. dollars over last year, and net
income increased 57 percent for fiscal 1997 to a record 93.9
million dollars, compared with the 59.7 million dollars in fiscal
1996.
</P>
<P>
As one of the U.S. leading retailers and resellers of personal
computers, CompUSA currently operates 133 chain stores in 61 major
cities throughout the country. Its marked increase in sales and
profits indicated a general trend in the PC market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
