<HEADLINE> National Games Usher in Reforms: Sports Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, August 13 (Xinhua) -- China's Eighth National Games,
to be held on October 12-24 in Shanghai, are of historical
significance as China has just celebrated Hong Kong's return to
the motherland, a top Chinese sports official said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters from China's southern provinces and Hong
Kong and Macao at a press conference, Yuan Weimin, vice minister
of the State Physical Culture and Sports Committee, said that
various reforms have been carried out to guarantee that Chinese
athletes could achieve better performance at the Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Medal sports set for the National Games have been cut down to
26 Olympic sports and traditional Chinese martial arts wushu. And
provincial delegations will have points added to their standings
total for any Olympic medal won by their athletes before the
National Games, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR), for
example, already had points because its star windsurfer Lee
Lai-shan won the first ever Olympic gold medal for Hong Kong at
last year's Atlanta Games, Yuan said.
</P>
<P>
Participating in the Games will be 46 delegations from China's
provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions, the People's
Liberation Army and various professions with a total of 7,700
athletes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
