<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Central Bank Hints at Rate Hike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The German central bank today
warned that it will steer its monetary policy towards arresting
substantial rises in consumer prices, an obvious hint that German
interest rates might be raised in the near future.
</P>
<P>
The central bank, the Bundesbank, said in its August economic
report that substantial rises in consumer prices in recent months
could not be overlooked.
</P>
<P>
"The Bundesbank will orient its policy in such a way that price
stability can be maintained," the report said.
</P>
<P>
Germany's two benchmark rates, the discount rate and the
Lombard rate have been left unchanged at historical lows for more
than a year. The discount rate now stands at 2.5 percent, while
the Lombard rate is at 4.5 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
