<HEADLINE> Safety Record For East China Railway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, August 13 (Xinhua) -- As of 18:00 tonight, the
Hangzhou Railway Administration passed its 2,300 accident-free
days, a record in its 48-year history.
</P>
<P>
The local railway authority handles nearly 1,000 kilometers of
railways in east China's Zhejiang Province, where the
well-developed economy means that railways there are very busy.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of the new national train schedule took
effect on April 1, most trains have speeded up by 15 percent to 20
percent, making things more difficult.
</P>
<P>
To maintain the good safety record, more than 30,000 officials
and employees in the administration have worked hard to guarantee
safety to help avoid several potential accidents.
</P>
<P>
During the period of flooding this summer, they also kept their
safety record intact. 
</P>
