<HEADLINE> Beijing Housing Construction Maintains Steady Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Beijing, the Chinese capital,
has witnessed steady growth in housing construction with the
addition of 2.17 million sq.m. of floor space.
</P>
<P>
The new housing covering 550,000 sq.m. was completed by the end of
June. New construction and renovation projects will enable the
city to provide more spacious apartments for over 10,000 families
with per capita living space under four square meters.
</P>
<P>
Residential housing has accounted for 46 percent of Beijing's
real estate development in recent years. Construction of 10
residential areas is currently in full swing in the city's
suburban areas, with six projects scheduled for completion by the
end of the year.
</P>
<P>
Between January and June, the city initiated renovation projects
for an additional seven million square meters of dilapidated
housing, up seven percent on the previous year's period. The city
has already completed the renovation of housing covering 215,000
square meters since the beginning of this year.  
