<HEADLINE> EU Reports Modest Growth in Output </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Eurostat, the statistics arm of
the European Union, today reported that the 15-nation union has
registered a modest growth of industrial production in the three
months to April.
</P>
<P>
Spain, Sweden and Finland led the upward trend by posting
industrial production growths of 2.5 percent, 2.0 percent and 1.5
percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
In comparison, the growths in the United States and Japan in
the same period were 1.3 percent and 1.0 percent, according to
Eurostat.
</P>
<P>
The renewed growth was driven by consumer durable goods which
recorded a notably higher rate of increase at 2.5 percent in the
month of April alone as compared with 1.5 percent a month earlier,
followed by intermediate goods (1.2 percent), capital goods (1.1
percent) and consumer non-durable goods (0.4 percent).
</P>
<P>
Finland, Greece, Italy and Sweden have demonstrated
extraordinary growth rates in consumer durables industry,
registering increases by 5.7 percent, 3.5 percent, 3.4 percent and
3.3 percent respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
