<HEADLINE> 558 People Infected With HIV/AIDS in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The number of people infected
with HIV/AIDS in Indonesia increased from 550 in June to 558 by
the end of July, a health official said today.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, 371 are men, 167 are women and 20 of unknown sex,
said Hadi M. Abednego, director-general for the Eradication of
Contagious Diseases of the Health Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Among the 558 people, 421 have tested HIV positive, 59 are
suffering from full-blown AIDS and 78 have died, he said.
</P>
<P>
However, the actual number is estimated to be 100 times higher
than the number recorded at present and most of them had been
infected through sexual intercourse, either heterosexual or
homosexual, he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
