<HEADLINE> Ukraine To Boost War on TB </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian Prime Minister Valeriy
Pustovoitenko said his government would boost the anti-tuberculosis
program to curb the ever spreading disease in the country.
</P>
<P>
While visiting the F. Yanovsky Phthisiology Institute of the
Ukrainian Medical Science Academy, Pustovoitenko said his
government was paying special attention to the recent spread of TB.
</P>
<P>
Reports said 17 million Ukrainians, or one third of the total
population, suffer from pulmonary diseases. Among them, one
million are hit by TB.
</P>
<P>
Pustovoitenko singled out social and economic hardships,
inefficient implementation of anti-TB measures and lack of funds
as the main reasons for the spread of the disease. 
</P>
