<HEADLINE> German Food Company Targeted by Blackmailers Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 13 (Xinhua) -- A German food company has once
again been targeted by unknown blackmailers, who claim to have
poisoned the company's products.
</P>
<P>
Thomy, a German subsidiary of Switzerland's Nestle concern,
received an anonymous letter warning that its products in more
than 50 stores in 14 German cities have been poisoned, police said
late Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Police did not say how much the blackmailers demanded but there
were speculations that they were pressing for 25 million German
marks (13.5 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Police have not found any poisoned food so far.
</P>
<P>
The Frankfurt-based company has been targeted by blackmailers
since early 1996. Last April, police found several tubes of Thomy
mustard and mayonnaise poisoned with cyanide in supermarkets in
the German cities of Saarbruecken and Regensburg, after receiving
a similar extortion letter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
