<HEADLINE> Iraq to Resume Oil Export Today </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The giant Liberia-flagged oil
tanker "Irvada" is getting prepared to start this afternoon
shipping Iraqi oil to world markets, Iraqi New Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The oil tanker arrived at the Turkish port of Ceyhan two days
ago, and its loading is due to take 30 hours after which it will
sail for a number of world markets.
</P>
<P>
Two other oil tankers will be arriving at the port of Ceyhan on
August 15 and 17 to ship more Iraqi oil, the agency added.
</P>
<P>
The Oil Refinery Company of Turkey has announced that it would
start receiving 8.1 tonnes of Iraqi crude oil as of August 20.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. Security Council approved on August 4 Iraq's new plan
for the distribution of food and medical articles in the second
stage of the oil-for-food deal which was signed in May last year
by Iraq and the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
The first stage of the oil-for-food deal went into effect last
December and on June 8 the U.N. Security Council agreed to extend
it fo another six months.
</P>
<P>
The deal allows Iraq to export 2 billion U.S. dollars worth of
oil overy six months to buy food and medicine for its people hard
hit by the U.N. sanctions imposed after Iraqi troops invaded
Kuwait in 1990. 
</P>
</TEXT>
