<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The Australian share market
closed more than one percent lower today as it felt the effects of
the 101 point drop on Wall Street overnight.
</P>
<P>
On Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial average ended 101.27
points lower at 7960.84.
</P>
<P>
"The industrial sector really weighed heavily on the local
market today while the resources sector staged a strong recovery
in the afternoon," broker Richard Gregory said.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index closed down 26.9 points at 2623.6 off
a low of 2604.8. It was the market's lowest close since June 11
when the all ordinaries closed at 2613.7.
</P>
<P>
The all resources index lost 6.8 points to 1383.5, clawing back
from a low of 1368.5, and all industrials index plummeted 51.2
points to 4215.3.
</P>
<P>
Bank and insurance stocks led the falls with the related
indexes down 48.4 and 58.2 points to 4972.3 and 6200.0
respectively.
</P>
<P>
National Australia Bank was 25.5 cents lower, Westpac lost 14
cents a share, Commonwealth Bank was nine cents lower, while ANZ
Bank gained four cents a share.
</P>
<P>
The resource sector staged an afternoon recovery with market
bellwether BHP gaining 11 cents to 17.13 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The gold index eased 16.1 points to 1285.9, spot gold bullion
was trading 75 US cents up at 328.00 US dollars an ounce.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totaled 477.86 million shares with a value of
939.02 million Australian dollars (699.56 million US dollars).
Falling stocks outnumbered rising stocks by 774 to 352.  
</P>
</TEXT>
