<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Citibank, one of the major
banks in Hong Kong, is introducing a brand new range of
enhancements for its Gold Card holders.
</P>
<P>
The enhancements include extra home protection, unique travel
privileges and a higher credit limit, Sunny Cheung, general
manager for Citibank Card Products Center, told a press conference
here today.
</P>
<P>
The new Citibank Home Emergency Protector service will provide
protection for the common inconvenience that often occurs in and
around the home. For plumbing repairs, electrical breakdowns
reconnections, locks opening, and air-conditioning restarts,
Citibank Gold Card holders will receive assistance right away by
calling a 24-hour hotline, Cheung said.
</P>
<P>
Travel benefits include free access to airport lounges, free
travel inquiry and booking service, and hotel discounts of up to
50 percent at over 100 prestigious hotels over the world.
</P>
<P>
And to allow cardholders to enjoy greater flexibility in their
spending, Citibank Gold Card holders will be provided with a
credit limit of up to three times their current monthly salary,
Cheung said.
</P>
<P>
"Citibank is always looking for ways to provide more value
added benefits to our cardholders. We believe our new offerings
will make Citibank Gold Card the most desired gold card in the
market," he said.
</P>
<P>
Citibank is one of the leading card issuers in Hong Kong with
about 720,000 Citibank Visa, MasterCard and Diners Club cards in
force. 
</P>
