<HEADLINE> Kampala Grenade Attack Suspects Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Kampala police authorities has
arrested more than ten suspects launching grenade attacks in the
capital, local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
Police spokesman Bob Ngobi said in the operation from 5 a.m.
to 7 p.m. Tuesday, they also captured two stick grenades, a
sub-machine gun with two full magazines, a set of police uniform,
a walkie-talkie and 30 toy pistols.
</P>
<P>
The police also found a motorcycle suspected to be used by the
criminals in a grenade attack.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the motorcycle escaped in the operation. Further
investigation is still under way, and the spokesman refused to
give more details.
</P>
<P>
Three grenade attacks occured in Kampala earlier this month.
Ten people died and 72 were injured. 
