<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian President Meets OANA Delegates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad
Khatami today met with Guo Chaoren, president of the Organization
of Asia-Pacific News Agencies (OANA) and all delegates to the
ongoing 10th OANA general assembly.
</P>
<P>
This was the new president's first meeting with heads of 31
news agencies from 24 countries in the Asia-Pacific since he took
office on August 4.
</P>
<P>
Khatami said that countries of the South should believe their
abilities and rid themselves of the sense of inferiority through
cooperation among themselves as well as with countries of the
North.
</P>
<P>
He called on the Asia-Pacific news agencies to create a healthy
system for exchanges of news and information through the
employment of modern technology.
</P>
<P>
He expressed hope that OANA will grow day by day and further
enhance mutual exchanges and cooperation to advance mass media
cause and bring about a bigger role of news agencies in politics,
culture and economy.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of OANA's 31 member news agencies, Guo Chaoren, who
also is president of China's Xinhua News Agency, congratulated
Khatami on his being elected as president of the Islamic Republic.
</P>
<P>
The heads of the OANA members gathered in Tehran in a three-day
session to explore ways to enrich the vitality of organization in
the new world situation. The conference is expected to end
Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
