<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Exam Officer Faces Leak Charges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 13 (Xinhua) -- An officer of the Hong Kong
Examinations Authority has been accused of leaking exam papers to
a candidate sitting this summer's Certificate of Education
Examination.
</P>
<P>
The officer, alleged to have photocopied exam papers and passed
them to a close relative who scored "extraordinarily high marks"
in all eight exams, was expected to appear in court this morning,
local papers reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Independent Commission Against Corruption (ICAC) was called
in by the Examination Authority to carry out a two-week
investigation into the case.
</P>
<P>
The candidate's results were canceled. About 130,000
candidates in Hong Kong took the exams in May and June, and were
notified of the results in early August. 
</P>
</TEXT>
