<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian Armed Forces to Have New Advanced Helicopter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Indian Minister of State for
Defense N.V.N. Somu said today that the indigenously manufactured
advanced light helicopter (ALH) is likely to be inducted into the
armed forces in 1998-99 (April 1, 1998 - March 31, 1999).
</P>
<P>
In a written reply to the ongoing session of the upper house of
Parliament here, he said that the ALH would be sold on the
international weaponry market after its introduction in the Indian
armed forces.
</P>
<P>
The multi-role helicopter would be able to carry 12 passengers
with two pilots in normal configuration and 14 passengers in high
density configuration.
</P>
<P>
The twin-engine helicopter with several advanced technologies
is nearing completion, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
