<HEADLINE> Cameroun's Seminar on Mastery of Public </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, August 13 (Xinhua) -- A two-day national seminar was
held here to help Cameroun's officials improve their mastery of
public expenditure, local radio reported here today.
</P>
<P>
Participants, mainly senior officials of Cameroun's Ministry
of Economy and Finance together with budget managers took part in
the seminar which ended Tuesday, the report said.
</P>
<P>
For two days, the participants had acquainted themselves with
management instruments such as how to make budgetary choices, the
role of computer and public accountants in the management of
mastery public expenditure.
</P>
<P>
During the seminar, Edouard Mfoumou, minister of state in
charge of economy and finance, pointed out that mastery of public
expending is an essential factor of good governance.
</P>
<P>
The minister noted that the mastery of public expending is
imperative in Cameroun, given the country's growing and fragile
economy.
</P>
<P>
The national seminar came ahead of the annual meeting of the
officials of the Ministry of Economy and Finance due to hold in
Yaounde from today to tomorrow. 
</P>
</TEXT>
