<HEADLINE> Man Arrested for Threatening Bomb Attack in Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 13 (Xinhua) -- German police confirmed today that
they had detained a young man who claimed he had planted a bomb in
a hotel where German Finance Minister Theo Waigel was spending his
holidays.
</P>
<P>
A police spokesman was quoted by German media as saying that
the detainee, 23, admitted making an anonymous call to the Hotel
Ahlbecker Hof in the Baltic Sea resort of Ahlbeck on Monday
afternoon to warn of the bomb attack.
</P>
<P>
Waigel had to leave the building for two hours, but no
explosive device was found later.
</P>
<P>
The man admitted during interrogation that he just played a
"childish prank." 
</P>
</TEXT>
