<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Halts Huge Loan to Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank will not
disburse the 71.6-million-U.S.-Dollar structural adjustment
credit to Kenya until several conditions are implemented, the
Daily Nation newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
However, existing projects are not affected by the decision
although no new projects will be presented to the World Bank
board for approval until Kenya's social and political situation
has improved, said Harold Wackman, the bank's country director
for Kenya and Djibouti.
</P>
<P>
The bank fully supported the International Monetary Fund (IMF)
on its insistence on good governance and reduction of corruption
before release of its aid package, he stressed in a statement
issued Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He also specified measures including the privatization of the
country's telecommunications sector, progress in streamlining the
energy sector and putting in place the necessary framework for
economic growth as important conditions for Kenya to get World
Bank loans.
</P>
<P>
His statement is widely treated as a further indicator that
this east African country is in for a hard time over what is seen
as its slow pace of economic reforms and corruption.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the World Bank has approved the release of a
125-million-Dollar credit to expand Kenya's power system and
upgrade its geothermal resources.
</P>
<P>
But the World Bank has insisted on the revision of certain
clauses in the contracts for Iberafrica and Westmont, both of
whom are independent power producers, said Wackman.
</P>
<P>
Some of the clauses relate to environmental safety, fuel
supplies to the two producers and so on.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank is keeping a "close watch" on its current
projects given the prevailing adverse conditions, he said.
</P>
<P>
Late last month, the IMF froze its 215-million-Dollar aid
package to Kenya citing high-level corruption as a key reason,
which leads to a steep decline of the Shilling against Dollar.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
