<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 540 Indians Killed in Violence in One Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Indian Home Minister Indrajit
Gupta said today that a total of 540 people were killed and 118
others injured in the country's violent incidents by extremists
from July 1996 to June this year.
</P>
<P>
In a written reply to the upper house of Parliament here, he
said that Bihar state topped the list of states for violent
incidents with as many as 287 persons killed during the period,
followed by Andhra Pradesh where 220 people lost their lives in
such incidents.
</P>
<P>
Property worth over 160 million rupees (4.57 million U.S.
dollars) was also lost in these incidents, he said.
</P>
<P>
As many as 399 security personnel were killed in the insurgency
affected northeastern parts from August 1996 to July 1997. The
government has extended an open invitation to any group of
individuals, including militants, for talks without any
preconditions to discuss their legitimate grievances, Minister of
State for Home Mohd Maqbool Dar told the upper house today.
</P>
</TEXT>
