<HEADLINE> UAE First Satellite Contract to Be Awarded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, August 13 (Xinhua ) -- The contract for the Thuraya
(chandelier) mobile satellite, the first satellite of the Unite
Arab Emirates, will be awarded on August 26, an official said
today.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday (August 12) was the deadline for submission of final
bids by three companies competing for the project and the name of
the winner will be announced on August 26, Jamal al Jarwan,
marketing manager of the satellite project told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
The 850-million-dollar project was initiated by UAE's Emirates
Telecommunications Corporation (ETISALAT) at the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
French Alcatel telecommunications giant was excluded from
bidding in May, leaving three companies, Aerospatial of France,
and Hughes and Lockheed of the U.S., vying for the contract.
</P>
<P>
ETISALAT is the biggest shareholder of the project, owning 20
percent of the total shares; the rest are owned by other seven
Arab investors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
