<DOCNO> XIE19970813.0135 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigeria Restates Territorial Claim Over Bakassi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria has restated its
territorial claim over the Bakassi Peninsula, which is also
claimed by neighboring Cameroun.
</P>
<P>
The statement by Chief Mike Onoja, director-general of the
Ministry of Defense in Lagos came in expectation of impending
decision on the dispute by the Hague International Court.
</P>
<P>
Onoja made the statement at the opening session of the 1997
defense advisers annual conference Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Disputes over the peninsula has led to constant clashes
between Nigeria and Cameroun in the last few years.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria's claim to Bakassi is borne out of the indisputable
fact that the area is located at its southeast tip and at least
90 percent of its population are the Efik and Efut people of
Nigeria, Onoja said.
</P>
<P>
He continued that it is the discovery of oil in commercial
quantity that raised Cameroun's interests in Bakassi, who in 1971
established the Jubane district in the area.
</P>
<P>
Onoja condemned the the Marua declaration of 1975 which gave
Bakassi to Cameroun, adding that it is invalid because Nigeria
never ratified it.
</P>
<P>
He further said that Nigeria's preference for peaceful
resolution of the dispute should not been seen as a sign of
weakness. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970813.0136 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ramos Orders Release of Funds to Cope with El Nino </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Ramos has
ordered the release of 500 million pesos (18 million U.S. dollars)
to develop small water impounding projects to mitigate the effects
of the El Nino, a senior agricultural official said today.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture Secretary Salvador Escudero said that there will be
a 40 percent reduction in rainfall as a result of the El Nino
which is set to hit the country during the latter part of the
year.
</P>
<P>
The southern islands of Mindanao are expected to be greatly
affected by the decrease in rainfall and are one of the priority
areas where the Agricultural Department is fast-tracking its
irrigation projects.
</P>
<P>
Escudero said small river irrigation systems have been
completed in Mindanao while small water impounding projects
consisting of small farm reservoirs and shallow tube walls are now
underway.
</P>
<P>
The National Irrigation Administration has reported that two
river irrigation systems in the area have been completed and
several projects are going on to provide water to rice-producing
areas dependent on rain water.
</P>
<P>
The government has also taken other steps to help counter the
adverse effects of the El Nino including intensive information
campaign and dissemination of the proper techniques for the use
and management of impounding project.
</P>
<P>
El Nino is a large-scale oceanographic and meteorological
phenomenon that develops in the Pacific Ocean and is associated
with extreme climatic variability such as devastating rains, winds
and drought. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
