<HEADLINE> Thailand to Create Farm Futures Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Thailand is expected to have its
first agriculture futures market soon as the government gave the
green light to the establishment of the market.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet recently has approved the setting up of the
independent organization, which will be managed like the Stock
Exchange of Thailand, a senior Thai Commerce Ministry official
said.
</P>
<P>
However, the budget of 1 billion baht (about 30 million U.S.
dollars) earmarked earlier for the establishment of the market
will be cut in line with the government's policy to tighten
spending, according to Siripol Yodmuangcharoen, director general
of the Internal Trade Department.
</P>
<P>
The department will choose to lease equipment rather than buy
it to create the market, while urging the private sector to
participate in the scheme, Siripol was quoted as saying by local
newspapers today.  
</P>
