<HEADLINE> Overall Inflation Drops in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Overall inflation continued to
fall last month due to improved supplies of basic food following
increased agricultural production, according to the August issue
of Monthly Economic Review by the Central Bank of Kenya.
</P>
<P>
The overall month-on-month inflation declined to 4.9 percent
in July compared with 10.2 percent in May and 7.6 percent in
June, said the magazine of the bank.
</P>
<P>
However, recent street violence have weakened the confidence
of investors in Kenya's economy, it noted.
</P>
<P>
Although the inflation is still under control, the Shilling
exchange rate weakened against all major currencies after the
worst political rest in seven years which claimed 13 lives around
this east African country. 
</P>
