<HEADLINE> Chad Urged to Come Back to Correct Position on Relations with China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 13 (Xinhua) -- China today urged the Government
of Chad to stick to the principles enshrined in the communique on
the establishment of China-Chad relations and come back to the
correct position.
</P>
<P>
When asked to comment on Taiwan's restoring "diplomatic
relations" with Chad, Foreign Ministry spokesman Shen Guofang
warned that the Chinese Government would take "necessary
countermeasures."
</P>
<P>
While stepping up their pursuit for "two Chinas" or "one China,
one Taiwan", Shen said, the Taiwan authorities have practiced
"money diplomacy" and sought so-called "diplomatic recognition" by
taking advantage of the temporary economic difficulties of some
African countries.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese Government will make no compromise at all when it
comes to such issues of principle as state sovereignty and
national unity," the spokesman said, adding that China is
resolutely opposed "to any acts of the Taiwan authorities aimed at
splitting the motherland."
</P>
<P>
"We are also opposed to the development of official relations
of whatever form between countries having diplomatic relations
with us and Taiwan," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
"We will never accept 'dual recognition'," he said.
</P>
<P>
Shen said that the Government of Chad, on the issue of its
relations with China, "should adhere to the principles expounded
in the communique on the establishment of the diplomatic relations
between the two countries and come back to the correct position,
or it will face the necessary countermeasures by the Chinese
Government." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
