<HEADLINE> S. Africa, Netherlands Sign Welfare Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 13 (Xinhua) -- South Africa and the
Netherlands have signed a memorandum of understanding to exchange
technology and expertise in the social welfare sector, a local
daily The Citizen reported today.
</P>
<P>
The memorandum was signed Tuesday in Pretoria by South African
Welfare Minister Geraldine Fraser-Moleketi and her Dutch
counterpart Erica Terpstra, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the signing ceremony, Fraser-Moleketi said the
occasion was preceded by extensive government-to-government talks
over the past two years.
</P>
<P>
"The signing of the historic memorandum of understanding
underscores my commitment and that of my Dutch counterpart to
development and cooperation as we take social welfare to the new
millennium," she said.
</P>
<P>
The memorandum encourages cooperation between social welfare
training institutions through, among others, the granting of
scholarships and exchange programs, and the transfer of
information on welfare policies and legislation.
</P>
<P>
It also supports the exchange of knowledge, technology,
experience and scientific expertise, as well as senior policy
makers, experts and practitioners. 
</P>
