<HEADLINE> Seoul Mayor Cho Formally Announces Presidential Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Seoul Mayor Cho Soon formally
declared today that he would run in the South Korean presidential
election in December, representing the minor Democratic Party.
</P>
<P>
Cho said that he had an obligation to serve the public in a
higher capacity and he would devote himself to running the city
until his resignation as Seoul mayor before September 19, the
deadline for candidates to resign from their official posts.
</P>
<P>
Cho apologized to the citizens of Seoul for resigning before
his tenure expires in June 1998.
</P>
<P>
The mayor, who was a professor at Seoul National University and
deputy primer minister in charge of economy, informed two days ago
that he would campaign for the presidency.
</P>
<P>
He would disclose information about his election preparation
later on, said Cho.
</P>
<P>
With Cho's bidding declaration, the presidential election,
which has originally been a fierce bout between Lee Hoi-chang of
the ruling New Korea Party and rival Kim Dae-jung and Kim
Jong-pil, is likely to be thrown into a new phase of disarray.
</P>
