<HEADLINE> Guangdong's Township Enterprises Maintain Steady Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Township enterprises in
China's more developed province of Guangdong reported a 22 percent
increase in output value in thee first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Their output value amounted to 260 billion yuan in output
value during that period.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the sector exported 70 billion yuan worth-of goods
and made 12.4 billion yuan in profits, rising by 26 percent and
12.5 percent, respectively, in the same period.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong has stepped up its efforts to create investment
opportunities.
</P>
<P>
As a result, Huizhou City signed 192 contracts with partners at
home and abroad, involving 1.1 billion yuan, 918 million of which
came from overseas funding.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong also adopted a strategy to produce name-brand goods
made by township enterprises, aiming to push the sector to a
higher level of competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
And efforts have been made to promote agriculture-related
township businesses. In Shaoguan, more than 80 farm produce and
by-product centers have been built to promote the cultivation of
high-yield crops.
</P>
<P>
In the mountainous Meixian area, townships and villages have
set up 1,268 businesses and cultivated 5,300 ha of hillside land
to grow crops. Consequently, the quality of life has improved for
people in 80 percent of these places.  
</P>
</TEXT>
