<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Successful in Greening Its Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, August 13 (Xinhua) -- China has made progress in
creating more green space in its cities, with the area of urban
green belts reaching 494,000 hectares and the greenery coverage
rate coming to 24.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Recent statistics show that the country's public green belts
cover a total area of 100,000 hectares and the average urban
greenery area per capita stands at 5.3 sq.m..
</P>
<P>
Twelve cities, including Beijing and Dalian, report a greenery
coverage rate in excess of 45 percent. Their average urban
greenery area per capital is double that of the rest of the
country's.
</P>
<P>
East China's Shandong Province has 246 parks, over 150 more
than that six years ago. And northeast China's city of Dalian has
more than 20 parks.
</P>
<P>
The living environment of the Chinese people is improving, and
so is their quality of life, said Zhao Baojiang, deputy minister
of the Ministry of Construction.  
</P>
</TEXT>
