<HEADLINE> Guangdong Leads in Patent Application, Registration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 13 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
Province has the largest groups of patent applicants and owners in
the country since 1995, according to sources at the provincial
patent office.
</P>
<P>
In the first six months of this year, the local patent
authorities received nearly 5,000 patent applications; the figure
is expected to reach 12,000 for the whole year.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, Guangdong has given priority to the use of
patented technology, which has pushed forward the local industries
and helped local products sell well on both domestic and
international markets.
</P>
<P>
The province has issued the country's first local law on patent
protection rights as well as preferential policies on taxes for
use of patented technology.
</P>
<P>
A complete service network for patent registration,
administration, protection and training has taken shape in the
province. 
</P>
