<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Tourist Industry Booms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzanian tourist
industry has boomed in the last few years with its earning rising
from 120 million U.S. Dollars in 1992 to 326 million Dollars in
1996.
</P>
<P>
As for the tourist arrivals, the figure has increased from
200,000 to 880,000 in the same period, according to a latest
statement made by Hatim Karimjee, board chairman of the Tanzania
Tourist Corporation (TTC).
</P>
<P>
Karimjee said in the statement that the tourist expenditure
per capita has also increased from 600 to 988 Dollars, which
represents a considerable success, with planned increment growth
to continue in future.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the TTC board's overall strategy on tourism
promotion and development is in line with the existing policy
guideline to promote quality tourism through low volume and high
yield.
</P>
<P>
"Every effort is being made to increase tourism revenue
through higher tourist expenditure per capita and
diversification," the TTC boss said.
</P>
<P>
Tanznia's traditional tourism product is wildlife. However,
steps are being taken to encourage investments in coastal and
cultural tourism in this east African country. 
</P>
