<HEADLINE> 11-Year-Old Student Rescues Four Boys in Water </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, August 13 (Xinhua) -- An 11-year-old primary school
student in a small village in Zhaotong City of southwest China's
Yunnan Province recently rescued four boys who accidentally fell
into a shallow pond.
</P>
<P>
On July 23, six-year-old Huang Nianqing slipped into a more
than two-meter-deep pond while walking to his home. The four other
boys who were with him jumped into the water holding hands to save
their friend.
</P>
<P>
They shouted for help, when they found that the water could
submerge their heads. Xu Shengyou, 11, who was bicycling past the
pond, jumped off his bike and dove into the water to save the boys.
</P>
<P>
He pushed four of the boys onto the bank before he got too
exhausted to rescue Huang, the first to fall into the water. Huang
was drowned.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Youth League of the region has praised Xu for his
heroism and encouraged him to aim high in life and study hard.
</P>
<P>
The story of the boy's brave deed has been spread throughout
the province by the mass media. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
