<HEADLINE> Information Industry Developing in China's Southernmost Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, August 13 (Xinhua) -- China's southernmost province of
Hainan has announced it will name the information industry as its
pillar industry, and will do more to provide resources for the
sector.
</P>
<P>
A public information network opened in Hainan last year, the
first of its kind in China, connected with Internet and China's
economic information network.
</P>
<P>
As tourism plays a crucial role in Hainan, an experimental
international tourism booking system has been set up to provide
services for tourists, linking information nets between travel
agencies and hotels in the province.
</P>
<P>
A basic information network now in place in the province
includes systems for financial nets, public safety monitoring and
land resources information.
</P>
<P>
Hainan's information industry got its start in 1993, when the
province computerized the financial accounting systems among five
banks and IC card networks. 
