<HEADLINE> Guangzhou's Industrial Production Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Industrial production in
Guangzhou, capital of south China's Guangdong Province, scored
stable growth in the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Its industrial output value during the period totaled 84.3
billion yuan, a 14.7 percent rise from the same period of
last year.
</P>
<P>
Its industrial added value hit 23.4 billion yuan, a 14.5
percent increase, and the industrial sales/output ratio reached
96.6 percent, up 0.12 percent.
</P>
<P>
The city's manufacturers readjusted their product mix by
placing emphasis on production of consumer goods. Guangzhou's
light industrial output value rose 16.7 percent to 50.1 billion
yuan in the first half.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the city's large and medium-sized
enterprises grew faster than the smaller ones in this period. The
output value of large and medium-sized enterprises amounted to
42.8 billion yuan, up 18.5 percent, while that of the small firms,
rose by 14.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
The output value of products for export came to 24.4 billion
yuan, an 18.9 percent increase. 
</P>
