<HEADLINE> First Beijing Opera In Mongolian Language Staged in Hohhot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Beijing opera fans in Hohhot, the
capital of Inner Mongolia, were treated to their first opera
excerpts sung in Mongolian, when students from the Chifeng Art
School performed for them recently.
</P>
<P>
Students from the Inner Mongolian city of Chifeng performed
traditional Beijing opera excerpts from a story about a woman who
is treated wrongly during the Ming Dynasty, about 400 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Artists in the minority region have talked about performing
Inner Mongolian versions of Beijing opera for many years, but
translations of the libretti were almost impossible to do.
</P>
<P>
Without understanding the Beijing accent, most people have
difficulties in appreciating the "quintessence of the national art
form", local artists explain.
</P>
<P>
Chifeng has a large Mongolian population and student performers
in the city worked hard at rehearsals of the well-known Beijing
opera excerpts.
</P>
<P>
A young actor and an actress, 13 years of age, were praised by
critics for their successful performances. 
</P>
