<DOCNO> XIE19970813.0189 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Production Materials Market Remains Stable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 13 (Xinhua) -- China's production materials
market remained stable in July, with sufficient supply, sluggish
demand, and prices going down.
</P>
<P>
According to the China Materials Information Center under the
Ministry of Internal Trade, of the 39 representative steel
products monitored, 25 recorded a drop in price in July compared
with the previous month.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Metallurgical Industry reported that in the
first six month of this year, the price of steel products for
construction dropped by one to three percent.
</P>
<P>
The sharp increase in production capacity and the output and
slowed demand forced producers to cut prices, triggering the
downturn in the market, analysts said.
</P>
<P>
As Chinese and overseas steel makers have been more actively
promoting their goods in coastal areas, the previously sharp
differences in steel prices have been eased between coastal areas,
where demand remains high, and the inland areas.
</P>
<P>
The steel market has also narrowed the gap between the
producer's price and the market price, a move initiated by
producers, analysts added.
</P>
<P>
The price of non-ferrous metals also continued to go down in
July, with the price of the five of the seven monitored products
falling, according to the center.
</P>
<P>
Of the chemicals, among the 39 monitored products, prices went
down for 27.
</P>
<P>
On the fuel market, prices of the coal and diesel oil fell
while that of petrol rose slightly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
