<HEADLINE> China Has 574 Nature Reserves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 13 (Xinhua) -- China has so far established 574
nature reserves, the third-highest total worldwide, according to
the Ministry of Forestry.
</P>
<P>
The reserves have helped to protect the country's ecological
systems and more than 1,000 species of rare plants and animals.
</P>
<P>
China has 470 varieties of wild plants in 30,000 different
species, accounting for one tenth of the world's total. About
10,000 of them are indigenous to China.
</P>
<P>
To safeguard them, the country has set up more than 400 rare
plant breeding centers, seeds banks, more than 100 national-level
botanical gardens and 13,000 hectares of plant seed cultivation
areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
