<HEADLINE> Warsaw Population Decreasing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The population of Warsaw,
Poland's capital, decreased by 5,000 to 1.63 million in 1996, the
city's Statistical Bureau said today.
</P>
<P>
The decrease resulted from more deaths than births and a small
number of new-comers moving to the city.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the number of persons who died exceeded the number of
new-born babies by about 7,000, and only 2,111 people moved into
the city, statistics showed.
</P>
<P>
Warsaw's population began to dwindle in the early 1990s. The
city's population in 1996 was 20,000 less than that in 1990.
</P>
</TEXT>
