<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Issues Poverty Relief Fund Management Measures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The State Council recently
issued a notice to expand the 15-article "State Poverty Relief
Fund Management Measures" which went into effect on August 1.
</P>
<P>
The measures, worked out by the Leading Group in Charge of
Aid-the-poor Projects under the State Council, are meant to
stretch the limited poverty relief fund so that the poor people in
rural areas have sufficient food and clothing and the economies of
poverty-stricken areas are developed.
</P>
<P>
The fund comes mainly from the central government and state
loans. It can only be used in the State-designated poor counties
to improve agricultural production conditions, develop diversified
businesses, build roads, create educational opportunities and wipe
out illiteracy, and provide drinking water, according to the new
guidelines.
</P>
<P>
Local governments are required to increase spending on poverty
alleviation, with local support going to the State-recognized poor
counties accounting for 30-50 percent of the State-allocated
capital.
</P>
<P>
Any province that fails to pay its proportion will suffer from
a fund deduction the following year, and in the event funds are
misappropriated, the money will be recovered and the people
involved will be punished, according to the rules. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
