<HEADLINE> China Attracts More Overseas Investment in First Half Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 13 (Xinhua) -- China saw overseas investment
rise 15.75 percent during the first seven months of this year,
today's "China Daily" reports.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation indicate that between January and July China drew a
total of 26.01 billion U.S. dollars in overseas investment,
compared with 22.48 billion dollars in the corresponding period
last year.
</P>
<P>
Committed overseas investment actually leaped 8.9 percent to
24.3 billion dollars during the period, the paper says.
</P>
<P>
Solely overseas-funded enterprises and Sino-foreign cooperative
enterprises attracted a large amount of capital in the first seven
months of this year, with growth of 26.65 percent and 15.02
percent, respectively. 
</P>
