<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Rupiah Plunges by 40 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's currency of rupiah
decreased Tuesday by 40 points against the U.S. dollar, but
Jakarta share prices increased slightly in a technical rebound,
local press today quoted analysts as saying.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian currency began at 2,610 rupiah per dollar,
dropped until 2,650 at noon, and closed at 2,638.
</P>
<P>
The closing figure passed the normal exchange equilibrium set
up by Bank Indonesia between 2,555 rupiah and 2,610 rupiah.
</P>
<P>
Foreign exchange dealers said the further weakening of the
rupiah was triggered by falls in the Singapore dollar and
Malaysian ringgit.
</P>
<P>
However, Coordinating Minister for Economic and Development
Supervision Saleh Affif said Tuesday that the rupiah fluctuation
was still normal. "We have not need to intervene and we do not yet
plan to enlarge its spread."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, share prices on the Jakarta stock exchange rose 0.7
percent, with composite index closing 4.77 points firmer to 662.94
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Securities analysts said Tuesday's rise in stock prices was
just a technical bounce after a sharp plunge in the past few days.
</P>
<P>
Sources at Bank Indonesia predicted that the rupiah and other
currencies of ASEAN (Association of Southeast Asian Nations)
countries are expected to return to normal after the International
Monetary Fund (IMF) moved to help stabilizing the Thai baht.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia helps the stabilization program by giving 500 million
U.S. dollars to Thailand through the IMF.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah fluctuation began on July 11 after Bank Indonesia
enlarged spread of rupiah exchange rate from 8 percent to 12
percent. The lowest plunge took place on July 21 when the rupiah
dropped to 2,660 per U.S. dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
