<HEADLINE> Ukrainian-European Union Summit to Be Held in Kiev </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, August 12 (Xinhua) -- A summit between Ukraine and the
European Union (EU) will be held in Kiev on September 5, a senior
official announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press briefing, Ukraine's Deputy Foreign Minister
Boris Gudyma said the summit will focus on the possibility of a
Ukrainian membership in the EU, and discuss a draft agreement
between Ukraine and the EU.
</P>
<P>
Gudyma said the agreement, probably the most important
post-Soviet one after the NATO-Ukrainian Partnership Charter, can
address some fundamental issues, such as establishing relevant
procedures for a political dialogue between the two parties,
developing bilateral relations, creating a basis for mutually
beneficial cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Ukraine attaches special importance to
obtaining the status of a nation with transitional economy.
</P>
<P>
He added that Ukraine will be required to join the World Trade
Organization (WTO), harmonize its legislation and carry out
cardinal reforms of its economy.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine's membership of the WTO is possible next year, Gudyma
disclosed.
</P>
<P>
Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma, Ukrainian Prime Minister
Valeriy Pustovoitenko, Luxembourg's Prime Minister Jean Claude
Junker -- the current EU presidency, and European commission
Chairman Jacques Santer will attend the summit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
