<HEADLINE> Boat Sinks in Indonesia, 20 Missing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- A fishing vessel capsized on
Monday in the waters off Pandegelang, Indonesia's West Java
province, leaving 20 people missing, officials said.
</P>
<P>
Only three of the 23 fishermen on board were rescued Tuesday
morning when they were hanging upon a bamboo polo to survive,
Antara news agency today quoted official sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
The boat capsized and sank after it was hit by a heavy wave in
the Sunda strait.
