<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Indian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Indian newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
The Hindustan Times
</P>
<P>
-- Well-known film producer and owner of T-series cassettes,
Gulshan Kumar, was shot dead by four unidentified men in Mumbai
(Bombay) Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Times of India
</P>
<P>
-- Nearly 140 persons were feared to have been washed away in
flash floods in Shimla and Kinnaur districts in Himachal Pradesh
of northwestern India Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
The Statesman
</P>
<P>
-- A "disunited" government came under attack in both houses of
parliament Tuesday for its failure to legislate on reservation of
one-third seats for women in the Lok Sabha ( lower house of
parliament) and state assemblies.
</P>
<P>
The Economic Times
</P>
<P>
-- The government has decided to import seven million pieces of
one rupee coins and three million pieces of two rupee coins to
overcome the shortage.  
</P>
