<HEADLINE> China Takes Eight More Golds in World Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese athletes reapt
their juicy harvest by taking eight more gold medals in Lahti on
Tuesday as the World Games was halfway in its agenda.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese fin swimmers chopped up five more golds and three
silvers to continue their gold-collecting trend following a record
of 5-4-2 the day before.
</P>
<P>
The gold medalists for China were Wu Xiaohui in women's 100
meter, Wang Yan in 400m, Li Shaozhen in 50m bated breath, Li Yong
in men's 100m and the women's 4x100m raley team.
</P>
<P>
So far, the Chinese swimmers had a lion's share of 10 golds,
seven silvers and two bronzes in 16 events.
</P>
<P>
"However, we are lack of young potentials and face tough
challenges from Russia and east European countries who have made
great progress in the sport," said Liu Qing, manager of Chinese
fin swimming team.
</P>
<P>
The other three golds for China were from the acrobatics
gymnastics wherein Russia took six golds, followed by Ukraine with
three, Belarus one. 
</P>
</TEXT>
