<HEADLINE> Tirana Win Albanian Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Tirana was awarded the 1996-97
Albanian league title on Tuesday after rivals Flamurtari was
penalised by Albanian soccer federation.
</P>
<P>
Flamurtari walked off the pitch 15 minutes into the second half
of the decisive match against Tirana last Sunday after having a
penalty disallowed with Tirana leading 1-0.
</P>
<P>
The team, two points ahead of Tirana going into the match, then
was slashed four points, fined heavily and had two coaches
suspended for two years.
</P>
<P>
The soccer federation also judged the game as a 2-0 victory for
Tirana. 
</P>
