<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0200 GMT, August 13 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIDAIHE, Hebei -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin, meeting
Tuesday with Samuel R. Berger, assistant to the U.S. President for
National Security Affairs, described the general atmosphere of
Sino-U.S. relations as good.
</P>
<P>
"Since my meeting with President Clinton in Manila last
November, relations between the two countries have had positive
progress, with common ground in many fields," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Li Peng, in his meeting with Berger, said that
the healthy advancement of Sino-U.S. relations is good for both
sides and has a far-reaching influence on world peace and
development.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen also met with
Berger. He said that President Jiang Zemin's upcoming visit to the
U.S. in the fall will symbolize the beginning of a new development
stage in Sino-U.S. relations.
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- Afghanistan will need 170,000 tons of
emergency food aid for some 1.75 million people in coming months,
despite its expected largest harvest in 18 years of civil strife,
U.N. food agencies reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
ROME -- Italy and Albania are discussing plans to deploy an
Italian force to assist Albania in rebuilding its shattered armed
forces, Italy's ANSA news agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
YANGON -- A total of 19 members of the National United Party of
Arakans, an anti-government ethnic armed group in Myanmar's
southwestern Arakan (also known as Rakhine) state, surrendered to
the government last month, The New Light of Myanmar reported
Wednesday. 
</P>
