<HEADLINE> Seles Continues Winning Streak in Maurier Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Monica Seles strode into
the third round by dispatching Asa Carlsson of Sweden with a 6-2,
6-4 victory in the du Maurier Open women's tennis tournament in
Toronto on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Seles who won the Los Angeles title two days ago, cornered
Carlsson, ranked 35th in the world, to commit 39 unforced errors
in the second-rounder.
</P>
<P>
Seles will next play No. 16 Sabine Appelmans of Belgium after
the latter beat Alexandra Fusai of France 6-3, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Jennifer Capriati, 21, the 1991 du Maurier champion who has
endured personal problems since, won her first-round match by
beating Silvia Farina of Italy 6-4, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Three seeds were upset Tuesday as Japan's Miho Saeki rallied
from one set down to overcome No. 9 Irina Spirlea of Romania 4-6,
6-3, 6-2, No. 14 Karina Habsudova of Slovakia suffered her defeat
of 6-3, 6-3 to Magdalena Maleeva of Bulgaria, and Japan's Naoko
Kijimuta upset No.12 Brenda Schultz-McCarthy of the Netherlands
6-4, 2-6, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
In other matches, No. 7 Conchita Martinez of Spain beat Japan's
Yuka Yoshida 6-3, 3-6, 6-1, eighth-seeded Anke Huber of Germany
romped Florencia Labat of Argentina 6-2, 6-1, and No. 11 Kimberley
Po downed Nathalie Tauziat of France 6-1, 7-6 (7-4). 
</P>
</TEXT>
