<HEADLINE> Ukraine to Lower Death Rate, Improve Pharmacy Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, August 12 (Xinhua) -- A lower death rate and an improved
pharmacy industry would be the government's health policy
priorities, Ukrainian Prime Minister Valeriy Pustovoitenko said
today.
</P>
<P>
The government must do a good job in people's health care for
human resources are the most valuable wealth of a nation,
Pustovoitenko said.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the average number of deaths each year in
Ukraine, a country with a population of 51.3 million, is about
800,000, while that for birth is 470,000.
</P>
<P>
Pustovoitenko attributed the growing death and decreasing birth
rates to low family income level caused by poor financial
situation.
</P>
<P>
Noting that tuberculosis (TB) is one of the major killers
threatening the Ukrainians, Pustovoitenko also urged
pharmaceutical factories to support the government's plan to
prevent and control TB by making more effective drugs.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show that 1 million Ukrainians are suffering
from TB, a disease that killed 8,200 in 1996 alone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
