<HEADLINE> South Africa Finishes Top at Hockey World Cup Qualifying </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 12 (Xinhua) -- South Africa topped the standings
table by gunning down New Zealand 6-4 in the final of the women's
field hockey World Cup qualifying tournament which concluded here
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Both South Africa and New Zealand have already qualified for
the World Cup finals to be held next year in the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
The top six teams, which also bracket Scotland, India, England
and China, all earned passports to the Netherlands through the
11-day tournament held in the Zimbabwe Capital.
</P>
<P>
China, despite losing to England in the 5/6 place playoffs
through tense penalty shootout on Tuesday, still squeezed into the
the last train to the World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Chinese coach Wang Qingsen said that the competition level of
the tournament had gone beyond his expectations.
</P>
<P>
"Chinese women's team used to have an edge over its opponents
as far as speed was concerned, now fastness has become the trend
in the game and the Chinese advantages have faded away," he said.
</P>
<P>
Wang also referred to the high altitude of Harare as partly
accountable for the "undesirable outcomes" of the Chinese team
which registered a 2-1-2 tournament record. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
